-- tf.h3: `Step 4`: Personalise the business card

To personalise the card with your information:

- Open `index.ftd` document from the `Code` tab on GitHub

- Click on the `edit` icon, to make the `index.ftd` document editable


-- ftd.image:
src: $assets.files.images.edit-index-ftd.png
width.fixed.px: 750
border-radius.px: 10
border-width.px: 1
border-color: $inherited.colors.border
margin-vertical.px: 16


-- tf.markdown:

**`Note`**: Now replace the default data with your information

```
Example 1:

`John Doe` with `Ajit Garg`, `Chief Executive Officer` with `DevRel` etc.
```
```
Example 2:

You can remove the property entirely if you do not wish to provide that data.
```
```
Example 3:

For `logo` replace `ipsum-logo.svg` with the file you uploaded 
(for example: in my case it was `fastn.svg`)
```

-- tf.markdown:

- Click on the `Commit changes...` button

- If you wish you can put detail about the changes in popup, else click on 
`Commit changes` again.



-- ftd.image:
src: $assets.files.images.personalise-the-card.png
width.fixed.px: 750
border-radius.px: 10
border-width.px: 1
border-color: $inherited.colors.border
margin-vertical.px: 16


-- tf.markdown:

The `Actions` tab will have new workflow running, wait for it to complete.

Once complete you can view your card by generating a live site on GitHub.


-- end: ftd.column



-- ftd.column:
width: fill-container
margin-vertical.px: 16

-- tf.h3: `Step 4`: Generate a live site for yourself

- Go to `Settings` 

- Select `Pages` from Table of Content

- Under Branch, click on the drop-down and select `gh-pages`

- Click on `Save`

This will build your GitHub pages and deploy your website.

To verify, go back to `Actions` and you will see a new workflow running, the 
latest will be `pages and deployment`. 


-- ftd.image:
src: $assets.files.images.gh-page-deployment.png
width.fixed.px: 750
border-radius.px: 10
border-width.px: 1
border-color: $inherited.colors.border
margin-vertical.px: 16


-- tf.markdown:

- Once it's complete, go back to `Settings > Pages` 

- You will find your live site as shown in the following image. To see your business card click on the button `Visit site`.


-- ftd.image:
src: $assets.files.images.live-site.png
width.fixed.px: 750
border-radius.px: 10
border-width.px: 1
border-color: $inherited.colors.border
margin-vertical.px: 16

-- tf.markdown:

There you go, you have created your personalised business card.

